headline: What The Latest Outlook Shift Means For Formula One Group's Valuation Narrative
summary: Formula One Group stock has received a modest price target lift, with the fair value estimate nudging up from $118.07 to $118.20 per share as expectations for its long term growth runway improve. The shift reflects slightly faster projected revenue growth, from 10.65% to 10.91%, as analysts grow more confident in the impact of expanding media rights, sponsorships, and global fan engagement. Investors can monitor these evolving assumptions and follow the changing narrative around this sports...

headline: Why Analysts Think Acuity Could Be Undervalued As Margins Strengthen And Market Assumptions Stay Cautious
summary: Acuity shares have seen their price target nudged higher as Street models absorb stronger recent execution and a steadily improving outlook for demand. With fair value estimates holding near $399.25 per share and only a slight reduction in the discount rate to 9.28%, the market narrative is shifting more on confidence and risk perception than on fundamental growth revisions.
